name: Bobby Bonilla Day
summary: Annually observed on July 1st, "Bobby Bonilla Day" commemorates a peculiar financial agreement between the New York Mets and former baseball player Bobby Bonilla. Despite retiring in 1999, Bonilla continues to receive an annual payment of $1.19 million from the Mets until 2035. This arrangement stems from a deferred salary contract negotiated in 2000. The Mets' decision to spread out Bonilla's compensation has been widely discussed, with some critics questioning its financial wisdom. However, the deal has become a topic of festive celebration among Mets fans, particularly on July 1st, which has been dubbed "Bobby Bonilla Day." The occasion has even extended beyond baseball, with other professional sports teams and players referencing the unique financial agreement.

name: Jayson Tatum
summary: Jayson Tatum, star forward for the Boston Celtics, has agreed to a record-breaking contract extension worth $314 million over five years. This deal sets a new mark for the highest NBA contract in history, surpassing the previous record held by Giannis Antetokounmpo. Tatum's decision to stay with the Celtics signals his commitment to the team and his belief in their championship aspirations. The contract solidifies Tatum's status as one of the brightest young stars in the league and positions him as a key player in Boston's future success.
